<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-11-24T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-11-24T15:00:00-05:00" n="1226" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1226">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">860C.01/11–2444: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Chargé to the Polish Government in Exile</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Schoenfeld</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-11-24T21:00:00+01:00">November 24, 1944—9 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received November 24—6:31 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Poles 124. Mikolajczyk has resigned as Prime Minister (see London’s
                                10326, November 23 from Harriman). Vice Premier Kwapinski
                                (Socialist) has been entrusted with the task of forming a new
                                Cabinet. Mikolajczyk’s resignation will probably not be announced
                                until tomorrow since there has not yet been time for the Polish
                                Government to frame an appropriate communiqué.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>[<hi rend="smallcaps">Schoenfeld</hi>]</signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>